# Patch 0032 — Workspaces settings pane + Restore-Archived picker + first-run
# pointers (ROADMAP Phase 3 UX; discoverability).
#
# WHAT: the final patch of the settings-consolidation trio (0030 top-right menu,
# 0031 Appearance/Customization panes, 0032 this):
#   - paneKavachaWorkspaces ("Workspaces"): a THIN pane over already-shipped
#     features — the tab-memory inactivity threshold pref KavachaTabMemory
#     watches (kavacha.tabs.unload-after-minutes, patch 0013) plus a manual
#     "Sleep inactive tabs now" (KavachaTabMemory.sleepBackgroundTabsNow, patch
#     0018); New-space-from-template buttons (gZenWorkspaces
#     .createWorkspaceFromTemplate, patch 0009); a "Restore an archived space…"
#     button; and an informational pointer to Snapshot/branch/timeline on the
#     menu and Cmd+K. Controller gKavachaWorkspaces, wired with Zen's own
#     four-file pane recipe (ADR 0021) alongside 0031's two panes. The
#     register_module template-inline guard already matches paneKavacha*.
#   - "Restore Archived Space" command in KavachaCommandRegistry BUILTIN
#     (ORGANIZATION domain; isAvailable = has archived spaces). Closes the gap
#     0018/0027 noted: the opener is clean now (gZenWorkspaces
#     .unarchiveWorkspace(uuid), patch 0009) — only a picker was missing, so
#     this supplies one via Services.prompt.select. Because 0030's menu is
#     generated from the registry, the command appears on the menu with no menu
#     edit. l10n key kavacha-action-restore-space.
#   - New-tab dashboard (patch 0011): a subtle "Settings" link (about:
#     preferences) so first-run users find settings without the palette.
#   - Welcome flow (patch 0017): a closing line on the final page pointing to
#     the new top-right menu ("Everything lives here").
#
# WHY: completes the settings-consolidation trio 0030-0032 and surfaces the last
# palette-only / menu-hidden features; restore-archived closes the
# 0018/0027-noted gap; the dashboard and welcome now point first-run users at
# the new menu.
#
# NOT BUILD-VERIFIED (no Firefox tree built in this environment). The new
# controller and the KavachaCommandRegistry edit pass `node --check`; the
# meta-patch edits (jar-mn / preferences-js / preferences-xhtml) keep their
# inner unified diffs count-consistent; the outer diff applies cleanly on top of
# 0031 with `git apply --check`. Applies on top of 0031.
#
# Touches: locales/en-US/browser/browser/preferences/zen-preferences.ftl;
# locales/en-US/browser/browser/zen-command-palette.ftl;
# locales/en-US/browser/browser/zen-welcome.ftl;
# src/browser/components/preferences/{jar-mn,preferences-js,preferences-xhtml}.patch;
# src/browser/components/preferences/kavacha-workspaces.js (new);
# src/browser/components/preferences/kavachaWorkspaces.inc.xhtml (new);
# src/browser/themes/shared/preferences/zen-preferences.css;
# src/zen/common/sys/KavachaCommandRegistry.sys.mjs;
# src/zen/welcome/ZenWelcome.mjs;
# src/zen/kavacha-newtab/index.html; src/zen/kavacha-newtab/newtab.css.
